g/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn The Handbook of Canadian Higher Education Law, experts examine key legal issues in postsecondary education. Establishing the current governance arrangements for Canadian postsecondary education within a historical context, the editors provide a detailed look at the legislative framework of postsecondary education and the role of the federal and provincial governments in organizing, regulating, and funding these institutions. Individual chapters analyze and expound on legal issues associated with institutional governance and management, identifying laws that define the rights and freedoms of faculty and students, and the obligations of the institutions towards them. Contributors engage with a wide range of issues associated with community activities - such as research ventures, knowledge mobilization, commercial activities, partnerships with industry, and land development projects that are hosted by postsecondary institutions. Presenting a wide range of documentary analysis and study of case law, legislation, regulation, and policy, this essential contribution to public policy determines current and emerging legal issues facing the academy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEducation, HigherxLaw and legislationzCanada. 0aEducation, Higher--Law and legislation--Canada. 0aUniversities and collegesxLaw and legislationzCanada. 7aLAW / Educational Law & Legislation.2bisacsh1 aBroshko, Li Jeen, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDavis, Brent, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilligan-Hackett, Patrick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHannah, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKraglund-Gauthier, Wendy L., eco